6 9-25-101. Definitions.
7
8 (a) As used in this section:
9
10 (i) "Diversity, equity or inclusion" means any
11 program, activity or policy that promotes differential or
12 preferential treatment of individuals or classifies
13 individuals on the basis of race, color, religion, sex,
14 ethnicity or national origin;
15
16 (ii) "Governmental entity" means the state, any
17 department thereof, the University of Wyoming and any
18 county, city, town, school district, community college
19 district, other political subdivision and other public
20 corporation of the state;
21
22 (iii) "Institutional discrimination" means any
23 of the following concepts:
2 HB0147

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0326
1
2 (A) That any race, color, religion, sex,
3 ethnicity or national origin is inherently superior or
4 inferior;
5
6 (B) That a person should not be
7 discriminated against or adversely treated because of the
8 person's race, color, religion, sex, ethnicity or national
9 origin;
10
11 (C) That the moral character of a person is
12 determined by the person's race, color, religion, sex,
13 ethnicity or national origin;
14
15 (D) That because of a person's race, color,
16 religion, sex, ethnicity or national origin the person is
17 inherently racist, sexist or oppressive, whether
18 consciously or subconsciously;
19
20 (E) That by virtue of a person's race,
21 color, religion, sex, ethnicity or national origin, the
22 person is inherently responsible for actions committed in
3 HB0147

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0326
1 the past by other members of the same race, color,
2 religion, sex, ethnicity or national origin;
3
4 (F) That fault, blame or bias should be
5 assigned to members of a race, color, religion, sex,
6 ethnicity or national origin, on the basis of race, color,
7 religion, sex, ethnicity or national origin;
8
9 (G) That any person should accept,
10 acknowledge, affirm or assent to a sense of guilt,
11 complicity or a need to apologize on the basis of the
12 person's race, color, religion, sex, ethnicity or national
13 origin;
14
15 (H) That meritocracy or certain traits
16 including a hard work ethic are racist or sexist.
17
18 (b) No governmental entity shall:
19
20 (i) Engage in any diversity, equity or inclusion
21 program, activity or policy;
22
4 HB0147

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0326
1 (ii) Engage in or require instruction in
2 institutional discrimination;
3
4 (iii) Require any student, employee or
5 contractor to attend or participate in any diversity,
6 equity or inclusion program or training or any
7 institutional discrimination program or training.
8
9 Section 2. Not later than July 1, 2025, all
10 governmental entities as defined in section 1 of this act
11 shall take any actions required to implement this act
12 including the promulgation of rules, if necessary.
